                            <comment id="371801" author="mdiep" created="Wed, 10 May 2023 16:53:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ake_s&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ake_s&quot;&gt;ake_s&lt;/a&gt;, could you please open an LU ticket and push the fix?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="371738" author="ake_s" created="Wed, 10 May 2023 06:02:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The change in 50517 is wrong in my opinion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct way would be to do&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#8212; a/lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4&lt;br/&gt;
+++ b/lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -147,6 +147,9 @@&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;egrep &quot;${O2IBDIR}$&quot; | head -n1)&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; if test -n &quot;$O2IBDIR_PATH&quot;; then&lt;br/&gt;
+ &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;if test -d $O2IBDIR_PATH/${LINUXRELEASE}; then&lt;br/&gt;
+ &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;O2IBDIR_PATH=$O2IBDIR_PATH/${LINUXRELEASE}&lt;br/&gt;
+ &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;fi&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; O2IBPATHS=$(find $O2IBDIR_PATH -name rdma_cm.h |&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; sed -e &apos;s/\/include\/rdma\/rdma_cm.h//&apos;)&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; fi&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using uname -r makes it impossible to build for anything else than the currently running kernel&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
